annotation.TEXT: Umm... Okay... You're right, game. I should only get one 1-up to make up for one death.

Oh, I know this place. But, since I'm not big, I'm not going to try to phase through the wall to reach the three 1-ups. I think it's technically possible while small, but it probably would require tool-assistance.
There's yet another 1-up handout.
Lucky bullet stomp there. Now, I'm not going to take this pipe this time, since it murdered me last time.
D'oh! Should've dropped down to avoid that cheepo. Also, I think bullet cannons don't work at all underwater.
Yes! I was hoping that pipe would take me to this sky bonus map!
...Game? ...Uhh... Whoops! The game just crashed! Alright, let me go back in time to when I got burned by the flame...
Aha!
Really, game? You're going to try to force me to take the pipe? Well, screw that! I'm super right now, so I don't have to play by your rules!
Whoa, I'm back here? Aw, man...
Wow, that's another bad failure. This better not turn into another 3-1 with all these failures!
Ooh, and there's another star, which is perfect, because I don't have fireballs to burninate Bowser with right now!
Boi- OW!!! Well, that didn't exactly work in my favor...
Oh, man. It looks like I'll need the star to get past that stationary fire bar! Better not dawdle!
Demo count: 15
Hey there, Toads. How's it going?
Now, I could wedge myself between the overhead blocks and the edge of the screen and climb up onto the roof, but I'm not gonna do that.
Whoa, a star! Oh, but it got itself jammed, just like a certain parakoopa I think back in 3-1. However, I think I can still collect it the same way I got that first flower! ...Yep, totally!
Whoa, big fire bar. Also, this level was short! And, nuts. I was late to the fireworks show again.
...And another!
Okay, yeah, that was totally on purpose to make up for those two 1-ups the game just gave me! Alright, now let's properly get this power up first...
Yes, timed it right this time!
Ow. That was a failed attempt to duck jump over the flame.
Okay, I think we're done with the Bowsers. Now, it looks like I might be able to jump over this flagpole, but I'm just gonna aim for the top of it and clear the level normally.
Also, those first two cannons at the start seemed to be nonfunctional for some reason, but these other cannons work perfectly fine!

Alright, next time, I'll be resuming my adventure in world 5-3! And, you guys get a sneak peek as usual, but it probably looks familiar, since it's gonna be the same map as 1-3. But, how will 5-3 differ from 1-3, if at all? Find out next time! To be continued...
That was a really good bullet stomp followed by a really bad failure.

And I guess I'll take the two 1-ups again, to make up for the two deaths I just had. (Wait, if those previous two deaths were to make up for the two 1-ups the game handed me, then... Umm... I'm confused...)
Now, unfortunately, because that invisible block is there, I don't see any way to reach that pipe. (I can think of a possible way to get to the pipe if I was big, but that's not happening now.)
Ha! I thought there might've been a hidden block there.

Okay, we've got a couple of parakoopas... with the green one being completely stationary? Yeah, this stationary green parakoopa is odd, not just because it stays in one spot, but also because it turns red when stomped on!
Another lucky stomp, and wait... I think this cannon-filled corridor is different from the one at the beginning of the level, so that bonus room must've actually sent me forward.
Please tell me that this is the ending staircase... Yeah, it looks like it.
DOUBLE KILL!
D'oh. I had it, but I didn't release down in time. Come on... I can get it again...

Whoa. Seems like 4-4's undergoing some renovations here. I hope the "maze" elements aren't still present, though they should be easy enough to figure out if they are. Oh, and once again, I'm staying down here even though I could easily have gone on the roof at the start.
I wonder why that message appeared this time, but not at the end of the first three castles?
Hello, and welcome back to New Strange Mario Bros.! Let's see how strange 4-3 ends up being!
Game crash count: 1 Space-time rewind count: 9
Oh, boy! Another 1-up!
Nuts. I kind of wanted to see what was in those bricks up there. Well, maybe I still can. Also, what's with the Bowser fire, a Toad, and a Bowser bridge being here?
Whoops, lost another flower, but at least it was the 1-up I ended up with!
Ha! If a power up is jammed in a solid block like that, you can often still collect it simply by jumping on the block it's stuck in.
Well, it's obvious what's gonna happen when I grab the axe this time!

Oh, boy! Another silly death!
Interesting place to emerge... Now, I wonder if I can get up to that pipe...
I'm checking for any potential hidden blocks here.
Nice! However, the pipe isn't enterable. Bummer.
...And another!
Another Bowser? Alright, I'll just burninate you too!
Whoa, we seem to have some balance lifts here. However, they're so low that it'll be impossible to break them for 1000 points.
Demo count: 14
Oh, wow. There really is a Bowser here! Well, fortunately, I can just burninate him easily.

The stationary color-changing parakoopa doesn't exist in the original SMB's usual levels, but I've seen it appear when using Game Genie codes to go outside of the original 8 worlds, and also in a few hacks.
Also, I do believe the first pipe here and the ones at the end all take me to the same place.
There was another one of those stationary color-changing parakoopas, and I managed to kill a Podoboo with it, but that Podoboo will respawn...
Okay, calm down. Just take this part nice and slowly...

Alright, finally! There we go! I do miss the ? block above, which probably held a power up, but that's okay.
Alright, I got through that obstacle. What's next?
Alright, let's try this again, and get two more 1-ups to make up for that previous death...
GAAAMMMEEE!!!

Alright, I'm back to where I felt the power of toasty, and now I won't take this pipe this time. Man, that was weird. I wonder why the game crashed, and why the recording decided to include the "Movie playback stopped." message there... Well, whatever.
Oh, that's interesting. I actually get the "Thank you Mario! But our princess is in another castle!" message this time!
Wow, what's with all the Bowsers around here?
Bah! Yet another hidden coin block getting in my way! However, I still think I can reach that pipe!
Aw, what?! Flying cheepos underwater again?
